11644  PropertyI64 mvGevSCBWControl;
11646 
11649  PropertyI64 mvGevSCBW;
11650  PYTHON_ONLY( %mutable; )
11652 
11659  static int64_type gevGetEffectivePayloadPacketsPerImage(
11661  const int64_type gevSCPSPacketSizeValue,
11663  const int64_type payloadSizeValue,
11666  const bool boExtendedID = false )
11667  {
11668  const int64_type PacketSizeWithoutEthernet = boExtendedID ? 48LL : 36LL; // 20 (IP Header) + 8 (UDP Header) + boExtendedID ? 20 : 8 (GVSP Header)
11669  const int64_type gevSCPSPacketSizeValue_effective = gevSCPSPacketSizeValue - PacketSizeWithoutEthernet; // The ethernet header is not taken into account here!
11670  return ( payloadSizeValue + gevSCPSPacketSizeValue_effective - 1LL ) / gevSCPSPacketSizeValue_effective;
11671  }
11679  int64_type gevGetEffectivePayloadPacketsPerImage(
11681  const int64_type gevSCPSPacketSizeValue,
11684  const bool boExtendedID = false ) const
11685  {
11686  return gevGetEffectivePayloadPacketsPerImage( gevSCPSPacketSizeValue, payloadSize.read(), boExtendedID );
11687  }
11689 
11696  static int64_type gevGetEffectiveBytesPerImage(
11698  const int64_type gevSCPSPacketSizeValue,
11700  const int64_type payloadSizeValue,
11703  const bool boExtendedID = false )
11704  {
11705  const int64_type PacketSizeWithoutEthernet = boExtendedID ? 48LL : 36LL; // 20 (IP Header) + 8 (UDP Header) + boExtendedID ? 20 : 8 (GVSP Header)
11706  const int64_type GVSPHeaderSize = PacketSizeWithoutEthernet + 14LL; // 14 (Ethernet Header)
11707  const int64_type GVSPImageLeaderSize = GVSPHeaderSize + 36LL;
11708  const int64_type GVSPImageTrailerSize = GVSPHeaderSize + 8LL;
11709  const int64_type protocolOverhead = GVSPImageLeaderSize + ( gevGetEffectivePayloadPacketsPerImage( gevSCPSPacketSizeValue, payloadSizeValue, boExtendedID ) * GVSPHeaderSize ) + GVSPImageTrailerSize;
11710  return protocolOverhead + payloadSizeValue;
11711  }
11713 
11720  int64_type gevGetEffectiveBytesPerImage(
11722  const int64_type gevSCPSPacketSizeValue,
11725  const bool boExtendedID = false ) const
11726  {
11727  return gevGetEffectiveBytesPerImage( gevSCPSPacketSizeValue, payloadSize.read(), boExtendedID );
11728  }
11730 
11737  static int64_type gevGetResultingBandwidth(
11739  const double acquisitionFrameRateValue,
11741  const int64_type gevSCPSPacketSizeValue,
11743  const int64_type payloadSizeValue,
11746  const bool boExtendedID = false )
11747  {
11748  return static_cast<int64_type>( static_cast<double>( gevGetEffectiveBytesPerImage( gevSCPSPacketSizeValue, payloadSizeValue, boExtendedID ) ) * acquisitionFrameRateValue );
11749  }
11751 
11758  int64_type gevGetResultingBandwidth(
11760  const double acquisitionFrameRateValue,
11762  const int64_type gevSCPSPacketSizeValue,
11765  const bool boExtendedID = false ) const
11766  {
11767  return static_cast<int64_type>( static_cast<double>( gevGetEffectiveBytesPerImage( gevSCPSPacketSizeValue, boExtendedID ) ) * acquisitionFrameRateValue );
11768  }
11770 
11781  static int64_type gevGetResultingPacketDelay(
11783  const double acquisitionFrameRateValue,
11785  const int64_type gevSCPSPacketSizeValue,
11787  const int64_type payloadSizeValue,
11789  const int64_type gevTimestampTickFrequencyValue,
11791  const int64_type bandwidthAvailable,
11794  const bool boExtendedID = false )
11795  {
11796  const int64_type bandwidthNeeded = gevGetResultingBandwidth( acquisitionFrameRateValue, gevSCPSPacketSizeValue, payloadSizeValue, boExtendedID );
11797  const int64_type packetsPerImage = gevGetEffectivePayloadPacketsPerImage( gevSCPSPacketSizeValue, payloadSizeValue, boExtendedID ) + 2; // one leader, one trailer
11798  const double totalDelayTime = 1. - static_cast<double>( bandwidthNeeded ) / static_cast<double>( bandwidthAvailable );
11799  const double interPacketDelayTime = totalDelayTime / ( static_cast<double>( packetsPerImage ) * acquisitionFrameRateValue );
11800  return static_cast<int64_type>( ( interPacketDelayTime < 0.0 ) ? 0 : interPacketDelayTime * gevTimestampTickFrequencyValue );
11801  }
11803 
11814  int64_type gevGetResultingPacketDelay(
11816  const double acquisitionFrameRateValue,
11818  const int64_type gevSCPSPacketSizeValue,
11820  const int64_type gevTimestampTickFrequencyValue,
11822  const int64_type bandwidthAvailable,
11825  const bool boExtendedID = false ) const
11826  {
11827  return gevGetResultingPacketDelay( acquisitionFrameRateValue, gevSCPSPacketSizeValue, payloadSize.read(), gevTimestampTickFrequencyValue, bandwidthAvailable, boExtendedID );
11828  }
11829 };

mvIMPACT::acquire::GenICam::DataStreamModule::mvResendMode
PropertyI64 mvResendMode
An integer property. Indicates the mode the internal resend algorithm is working in. This feature is a bit mask. The bits have the following meaning (LSB to MSB): Request Resends when a new block starts and the current one has missing packets(0x01)(not recommended for LAG), Request Resends when a new block starts and the current one has no trailer so far(0x02)(not recommended for LAG), Request Resends when more than 'ResendThreshold' packets have been received since a missing packet has been detected(0x04), Request Resends whenever 'mvResendResponseTimeout' did elapse for the previous still incomplete buffer(0x08), Request Resends whenever 'mvResendResponseTimeout' did elapse for the current still incomplete buffer(0x10), Request Resends whenever a packet is considered as missing(0x20)(not recommended for LAG), Request Resends whenever a block start has been missing(e.g. because no capture buffer was available at the time the block did start)(0x40)
